# PR #10868: PS-69087 Phase 9: harden Both-method FileShare coverage
**Tipo:** test
**Branch:** `wip/adam/PS-69087-phase9-coverage` → `wip/adam/tfc-prep-non-tc-files`

## Descripción
Hardens Indirect to Direct coverage for Both FileShare methods #3, #6, and #8 with explicit FileShare-side assertions in SyncPhotoToFMS, ProjectExportIntegrationTests, and SpecSetFromFMS. Updates coverage-progress.md Phase 9 section. No new test classes; playlist unchanged.

Made with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)

## Feedback de reviewers
[COMMENTED por @copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]]: ## Pull request overview

This PR strengthens Phase 9 of the PS-69087 FileShare coverage effort by adding explicit FileShare-side assertions to existing parallel integration tests for the “Both” FileShare methods (#3, #6, #8), and updates the coverage progress tracker accordingly.

**Changes:**
- Added FileShare assertions in `SpecSetFromFMS` to validate spec uploads result in expected files being written into the FMS directory.
- Enhanced `ProjectExportIntegrationTests` to assert the zip on disk matches recorded size and contains exported RFI content.
- Added a new `SyncPhotoToFMS` test to assert rotated photos are staged into `WebFileUploadDirectory` and match the `PhotosDirectory` source.

### Reviewed changes

Copilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 4 comments.

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/coverage-progress.md | Updates Phase 9 tracking details and checklist for FileShare-side assertions. |
| Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/Spec Management/SpecSetFromFMS.cs | Adds/extends assertions verifying spec-set uploads create corresponding FMS files. |
| Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/ProjectExport/ProjectExportIntegrationTests.cs | Adds assertions validating the created zip’s size and expected exported content. |
| Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/Photo Management/SyncPhotoToFMS.cs | Introduces a new test verifying rotated photos are staged to the upload directory with expected content. |
[Comentario en docs/temp/tfs-prep-non-tc-files/coverage-progress.md:1 por @Copilot]: The file now starts with a UTF-8 BOM (the invisible \uFEFF character before `#` on line 1). This can cause inconsistent rendering/diffs in some tooling; please remove the BOM so the heading starts with a plain `#` character.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/Spec Management/SpecSetFromFMS.cs:38 por @Copilot]: `m_SpecSet` is dereferenced (`m_SpecSet.FileVersionGUID`) before it’s asserted non-null. If `ProcessSpecSetAsync` ever returns null, this will throw a `NullReferenceException` and hide the real failure. Assert `m_SpecSet` is not null before using it, and keep that prerequisite outside the `AssertionScope` (per `docs/ai/INTEGRATION_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md` §3).
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/Spec Management/SpecSetFromFMS.cs:88 por @Copilot]: The per-file FMS assertions can give false confidence when uploads share the same length (the loop can match the same FMS file twice). Also, `Directory.GetFiles(...)` is executed once per expected file. Prefer snapshotting FMS files before the upload, then asserting the *new* files’ lengths match the uploaded sources as a multiset.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelIntegrationTests/Photo Management/SyncPhotoToFMS.cs:96 por @Copilot]: This test claims to verify that the staged upload file’s *bytes* match `PhotosDirectory`, but it currently only compares file length. Length-only checks can pass for different content with the same size; update the assertion to compare actual bytes (or a hash) to make the FileShare-side assertion meaningful.

